i dont usually post something like this but stepping into a decade (thats supposed to be) filled with monumental milestones and the so called best years of life alone 3409 miles from home conjured up a lot of feelings in me. no one warned me that i might develop a fear of turning the big two-oh so i really spent a day (not really) googling "how to deal with turning 20".‚Ä¨ old enough to have my own choices yet young enough to make the wrong ones i guess?
-
‚Ä™then the day came and went and i realized nothing significant changed. im still a college student on my spring break and although i went to seven eleven to pay my electricity and gas bill just like the other month i still depend on my parents for almost everything and still even had a hard time deciding what to eat. i mean the changes arent tangible, at least yet.‚Ä¨ perhaps its just the feelings it brought which are no different from the dread of each decade shift thereafter like 30th 40th and so on?‚Ä¨
-
‚Ä™and just one day prior i heard a sad news that one of my classmates in middle school just passed away and it got me thinking of how fragile life is. so above all i hope im growing up appreciating life to the fullest and not just getting old to enter another decade not doing my best.
-
also thanks for everyone's wishes i didnt expect them all when i turned off my birthday notification everywhere hehe thank you!!üíï (also thanks for reading)

caption.text:
when im on my own, i look for signs. sometimes theyre actually there, sometimes I make them up.

but most of the time, i cant tell the difference between the two.

üëåüèª
Life is too short to be waiting for somebody to act right.

I never enjoy anything.
I'm always waiting for whatever's next.

I think everyone's like that,
living life in fast forward,
never stopping to enjoy the moment,
too busy trying to rush through everything
so we can get on with what we're really supposed to be doing with our lives.

Then I get these flashes of clarity,
brilliant clarity,
where I stop and think:

Wait, this is it.
This is my life.
I better slow down and enjoy it
because one day,
we're all gonna end up in the ground,
and that will be it.
We'll be gone.
